{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, AI has great potential to tackle complicated optimization problems in a data-driven manner, which is emerging as a promising research direction [66,67].",
    "In particular, solving an optimization problem is essential to find the mapping from the problem statement to the corresponding solutions.",
    "Thanks to the powerful nonlinear mapping capability, AI, especially DL, can effectively model these sophisticated mappings.In addition, DRL has been widely used to deal with the Markov decision process (MDP), as in intelligent caching and unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) trajectory planning [68], demonstrating the advantages of satisfactory performance and low complexity.",
    "Specifically, DRL tackles long-term stochastic optimization problems in a trial-and-error manner, bypassing the complicated mathematical derivations [69].",
    "Moreover, the training samples are obtained via the interaction between the agent and the environment, and the training process is based on the temporal difference algorithm [70]."
  ]
}